The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Godrej Consumer Products Ltd has reported a 59.55 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 27.81 crore for the second quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 17.43 crore in the year-ago period. Total income has increased 19.93 per cent at Rs 163.13 crore against Rs 135.15 crore in the same period last fiscal, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The board has declared a second interim dividend of 75 per cent, or Rs 3 per share of Rs 4 each, for 2005-06.

 Lupin Ltd has posted a 158 per cent rise in net profit for the second quarter ended September 30 at Rs 45.2 crore against Rs 17.5 crore in the year-ago period. Gross revenues increased 32 per cent at Rs 419.1 crore against Rs 318.1 crore last year. The company also said Vijay Kelkar and R.A. Shah have joined as independent directors.

 GlaxoSmithkline Consumer Healthcare has declared an interim dividend of 80 per cent. The companys net profit rose 34 per cent to Rs 30.26 crore for the third quarter ended September 30, compared with Rs 22.58 crore a year ago. Total revenues were up 9.79 per cent at Rs 263.35 crore (Rs 237.97 crore).

 Polaris Software Lab has reported a 47.36 per cent drop in net profit at Rs 8.09 crore for the second quarter ended September 30 against Rs 15.37 crore for the same period last fiscal. Total income has increased 4.17 per cent at Rs 178.77 crore (Rs 169.68 crore).

 Cummins India has recorded a 29.93 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 37.76 crore for the second quarter ended September 30 against Rs 29.06 crore in the year-ago period. Total income stood at Rs 378.86 crore during the period against Rs 315.69 crore last year.

 SREI Infrastructure Finance Ltd has reported a 49.7 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 8.58 crore for the second quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 5.73 crore in the same period last fiscal. 

 Clariant (India) has reported a 37 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 7.2 crore for the quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 5.2 crore in the corresponding previous quarter. The company?s turnover stood at Rs 92.7 crore (Rs 84.4 crore).

 Helios and Matheson Ltd has posted a quantum leap in its net profit for the second quarter ended September 30 at Rs 9.06 crore compared with Rs 4.52 crore a year ago. Incomes rose to Rs 52.80 crore (Rs 28.46 crore).

 Blue dart Express has posted a net profit of Rs 17.66 crore for the July-September quarter against Rs 10.05 crore reported a year ago. Incomes stood at Rs 137.09 crore.

